cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for solving numerical inversion using digital memcomputing machines (DMMs) implemented with self-organizing logic gates (SOLGs). This involves solving linear systems and matrix inversion, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). However, the use of DMMs and SOLGs suggests a focus on emerging technologies (cs.ET) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The implementation of the method in hardware also suggests a focus on logic design and optimization (cs.LO) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS). Finally, the potential applications of this method in real-time computing suggest a focus on neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
